---
openapi: "3.0.1"
info:
  title: "VPD Returns"
  description: "This API specification defines the request and response data models\
    \ for managing Vaping Duty Returns.\n\nIt supports two core operations:\n  - Create\
    \ a Vaping Duty Return\n  - Retrieve an existing Vaping Duty Return\n\n The Create\
    \ Return API enables consumers to submit Vaping Duty Return data.\n Upon successful\
    \ processing, the API returns confirmation details including:\n  - Vaping Duty\
    \ reference number\n  - Total amount due\n  - Payment due date\n\nThe following\
    \ fields are returned where available:\n  - Submission ID\n  - Charge reference\n\
    \n The Display Return API enables consumers to retrieve previously submitted returns\
    \ using the Vaping Duty reference number and period key.\nThe API returns the\
    \ complete return details as stored in ETMP.\n\n  This API is implemented as a\
    \ synchronous RESTful service.\n\nChange Log:\n\n| Version | Date       | Author\
    \              | Description |\n|---------|------------|--------------------|-------------|\n\
    | 0.1.0   | 15-04-2025 | Nitin Chinthireddy | Initial draft of ETMP Vaping Duty\
    \ Return (EPID1714 v0.1 and EPID1715 v0.1) |\n| 0.1.1   | 12-05-2026 | Nitin Chinthireddy\
    \ | Updated API specification based on review feedback: aligned schemas,updated\
    \ endpoints, resolved inconsistencies, standardised naming and formats, resolved\
    \ schema-example mismatches, restored enum documentation, removed non-VPD artefacts,\
    \ and improved documentation clarity |\n| 0.1.2   | 28-05-2026 | Nitin Chinthireddy\
    \ | Updated API specification based on review feedback and VPD Return Data Items\
    \ v2.7: aligned request and response schemas using a single vapingProductsProduced\
    \ structure; removed legacy nilReturn/regularReturn representations; standardised\
    \ totalDutyDue model (replaced totalDutyDue with totalDue and ensured calculation\
    \ consistency); corrected and validated all request and response examples including\
    \ financial calculations and rounding; aligned otherOptions structure with duty\
    \ suspense fields; removed unused and redundant schema definitions; cleaned up\
    \ invalid and unsupported fields; improved example naming and readability; ensured\
    \ full schema-to-example consistency across Create and Display APIs. |\n| 0.1.3\
    \ | 04-06-2026 | Nitin Chinthireddy | Refined API based on Round 2 review: restructured\
    \ vapingProductsProduced to a return-level object with vapingProdManufactured\
    \ and returns array; standardised nil returns using empty arrays; aligned Create\
    \ and Display schemas; added mandatory declaration details; corrected duty suspense\
    \ handling (omit volumes when flag = '0'); updated all examples for schema consistency;\
    \ enhanced validation with updated taxType (^[A-Z0-9]{3}$) and periodKey (YYK[A–\
    L]); clarified schema descriptions and retained ETMP-aligned naming (reasonForUnderDecl).\
    \ |\n|0.1.4 | 10-06-2026 | Nitin Chinthireddy | Updated API based on Final review:\
    \ declarationType is updated with field lengths as per Data Items v2.9, chargeDetails\
    \ is made optional in vpdReturnDisplay Response Schema and Nil return example\
    \ for Display sample is updated|\n| 0.1.5 | 12-06-2026 | Nitin Chinthireddy |\
    \ Updated API to support signed values: introduced amountTypeSigned11_2 and applied\
    \ to adjustmentAmount and totalDue fields to allow both positive and negative\
    \ values; updated related field descriptions to clarify sign usage; corrected\
    \ calculation alignment in sample payloads |"
  version: "0.1.5"
  termsOfService: "http://INSERT_LINK_TO_SLA_HERE"
  contact:
    name: "SAP ETMP Integration Services"
  license:
    name: "Apache 2.0"
    url: "http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0"
  x-integration-catalogue:
    reviewed-date: "2026-04-15T12:00:00Z"
    platform: "HIP"
    publisher-reference: "EPID1714&EPID1715"
    short-description: "Consumer to ETMP Vaping Duty Return Create and Display "
    status: "BETA"
    backends:
    - "ETMP"
    domain: 2
    sub-domain: 2.21
servers:
- url: "http://etmp-egress-gateway.egress.svc.cluster.local"
  description: "Egress Gateway to ETMP TEST"
tags:
- name: "VPD"
  description: "Vaping Duty Return APIs"
paths:
  /RESTAdapter/vpd/returns:
    post:
      deprecated: false
      summary: "Create a Vaping Duty Return in ETMP"
      description: "This operation enables a consumer (e.g. MDTP) to create a Vaping\
        \ Duty Return in ETMP-SAFE via a synchronous interface.\n\n It allows vaping\
        \ duty customers to submit returns digitally, removing the need for paper-based\
        \ submissions to HMRC.\n\n Upon successful validation and processing in ETMP,\
        \ the API returns:\n \nMandatory fields:\n  - processingDate\n  - vpdReferenceNumber\n\
        \  - amount\n  - paymentDueDate\n\n  Optional fields (returned where available):\n\
        \  - submissionId\n  - chargeReference\n"
      operationId: "createVapingDutyReturn"
      tags:
      - "VPD"
      parameters:
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/correlationid"
      - name: "X-Message-Type"
        in: "header"
        description: "Fixed value identifying a VPD Return Create request."
        required: true
        deprecated: false
        allowEmptyValue: false
        style: "simple"
        schema:
          type: "string"
          enum:
          - "VPDReturnCreate"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/X-Originating-System"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/X-Receipt-Date"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/X-Regime-Type"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/X-Transmitting-System"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/X-ZVPD"
      requestBody:
        description: "Request structure"
        required: true
        content:
          application/json:
            schema:
              $ref: "#/components/schemas/VPDReturnCreate_Request_Schema"
            examples:
              Regular return example:
                $ref: "#/components/examples/VPDRegularReturn_CreateSample"
              Nil return example:
                $ref: "#/components/examples/VPDNilReturn_CreateSample"
      responses:
        "201":
          description: "Created"
          headers:
            correlationid:
              $ref: "#/components/headers/correlationIdResponseType"
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/VPDReturnCreate_Response_Schema"
              examples:
                Success Response example:
                  value:
                    success:
                      processingDate: "2026-05-08T10:30:00Z"
                      vpdReferenceNumber: "GBWK1234567WK"
                      submissionId: "123456789012"
                      chargeReference: "AB123456789012"
                      amount: 16277.63
                      paymentDueDate: "2026-06-07"
        "400":
          description: "Bad Request"
          headers:
            correlationid:
              $ref: "#/components/headers/correlationIdResponseType"
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/VPDReturn_SystemErrorType_Schema"
              examples:
                badRequest:
                  $ref: "#/components/examples/SystemErrorType_400Sample"
        "401":
          description: "Unauthorized"
        "403":
          description: "Forbidden"
        "404":
          description: "Not Found"
        "415":
          description: "Unsupported media-type"
        "422":
          description: "Unprocessable"
          headers:
            correlationid:
              $ref: "#/components/headers/correlationIdResponseType"
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/VPDReturnCreate_ETMPErrorType_Schema"
              examples:
                unprocessable:
                  value:
                    error:
                      processingDate: "2022-01-31T09:26:17Z"
                      code: "001"
                      text: "REGIME missing or invalid"
        "500":
          description: "Internal Server Error"
          headers:
            correlationid:
              $ref: "#/components/headers/correlationIdResponseType"
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/VPDReturn_SystemErrorType_Schema"
              examples:
                internalServerError:
                  $ref: "#/components/examples/SystemErrorType_500Sample"
  /RESTAdapter/vpd/returns/{vpdreference}/{periodkey}:
    parameters:
    - name: "periodkey"
      in: "path"
      description: "Period Key : \nPattern: \"^[0-9]{2}(KA|KB|KC|KD|KE|KF|KG|KH|KI|KJ|KK|KL)$\"\
        \nExample: 24KA\n"
      required: true
      deprecated: false
      allowEmptyValue: false
      style: "simple"
      schema:
        type: "string"
        pattern: "^[0-9]{2}(KA|KB|KC|KD|KE|KF|KG|KH|KI|KJ|KK|KL)$"
    - name: "vpdreference"
      in: "path"
      description: "Vaping Duty Reference Number.\n\n Pattern:\n - (GB|XI)WK followed\
        \ by 7 digits and suffix WK\n\nExample:\n  - GBWK1234567WK\n"
      required: true
      deprecated: false
      allowEmptyValue: false
      style: "simple"
      schema:
        type: "string"
        pattern: "^(?:GB|XI)WK[0-9]{7}WK$"
    get:
      deprecated: false
      summary: "Consumer to ETMP Vaping Duty Return Display Operation"
      description: "This operation enables a consumer (e.g. MDTP) to retrieve an existing\
        \ Vaping Duty Return from ETMP-SAFE via a synchronous interface.\n\nThe request\
        \ requires:\n  - Vaping Duty reference number\n  - Period key\n\n The API\
        \ returns the complete return details as stored in ETMP.\n This is implemented\
        \ as a synchronous RESTful operation.\n"
      operationId: "getVapingDutyReturn"
      tags:
      - "VPD"
      parameters:
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/correlationid"
      - name: "X-Message-Type"
        in: "header"
        description: "Fixed value identifying a VPD Return Display request"
        required: true
        deprecated: false
        allowEmptyValue: false
        style: "simple"
        schema:
          type: "string"
          enum:
          - "VPDReturnDisplay"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/X-Originating-System"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/X-Receipt-Date"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/X-Regime-Type"
      - $ref: "#/components/parameters/X-Transmitting-System"
      responses:
        "200":
          description: "Successful Get"
          headers:
            correlationid:
              $ref: "#/components/headers/correlationIdResponseType"
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/VPDReturnDisplay_Response_Schema"
              examples:
                VPD Regular Return Success Sample:
                  value:
                    success:
                      processingDate: "2026-05-28T10:30:00Z"
                      idDetails:
                        vpdReferenceNumber: "GBWK1234567WK"
                        submissionId: "123456789012"
                      chargeDetails:
                        periodKey: "24KA"
                        chargeReference: "AB123456789012"
                        periodFrom: "2024-01-01"
                        periodTo: "2024-01-31"
                        receiptDate: "2026-05-28T10:00:00Z"
                      vapingProductsProduced:
                        vapingProdManufactured: "1"
                        returns:
                        - taxType: "641"
                          dutyRate: 10.5
                          amountProducedLiquid: 1500.25
                          dutyDue: 15752.63
                      underDeclaration:
                        underDeclFilled: "1"
                        reasonForUnderDecl: "Incorrect reporting in previous return"
                        underDeclarationProducts:
                        - returnPeriodAffected: "23KB"
                          taxType: "641"
                          dutyRate: 10.5
                          amountUnderDeclared: 200.0
                          dutyDue: 2100.0
                      overDeclaration:
                        overDeclFilled: "1"
                        reasonForOverDecl: "Duplicate entry in prior submission"
                        overDeclarationProducts:
                        - returnPeriodAffected: "23KC"
                          taxType: "641"
                          dutyRate: 10.5
                          amountOverDeclared: 100.0
                          dutyDue: 1050.0
                      spoiltProduct:
                        spoiltProductFilled: "1"
                        spoiltProducts:
                        - returnPeriodAffected: "24KA"
                          taxType: "641"
                          dutyRate: 10.5
                          amountSpoilt: 50.0
                          dutyDue: 525.0
                      totalDutyDue:
                        totalDutyDueVapingProducts: 15752.63
                        totalDutyOverDeclaration: 1050.0
                        totalDutyUnderDeclaration: 2100.0
                        totalDutySpoiltProduct: 525.0
                        adjustmentAmount: 0.0
                        totalDue: 16277.63
                      otherOptions:
                        vapingProductUnderDutySuspense: "1"
                        volumeMovedFromDutySuspense: 300.0
                        volumeMovedToDutySuspense: 150.0
                      declaration:
                        fullName: "John Smith"
                        capacityInWhichSigned: "Director"
                        signeesEmailAddress: "john.smith@example.com"
                VPD Nil Return Success Sample:
                  value:
                    success:
                      processingDate: "2026-06-10T10:30:00Z"
                      idDetails:
                        vpdReferenceNumber: "GBWK1234567WK"
                        submissionId: "123456789012"
                      vapingProductsProduced:
                        vapingProdManufactured: "0"
                        returns: []
                      declaration:
                        fullName: "John Doe"
                        capacityInWhichSigned: "Finance Manager"
                        signeesEmailAddress: "john.doe@example.com"
        "400":
          description: "Bad Request"
          headers:
            correlationid:
              $ref: "#/components/headers/correlationIdResponseType"
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/VPDReturn_SystemErrorType_Schema"
              examples:
                badRequest:
                  $ref: "#/components/examples/SystemErrorType_400Sample"
        "401":
          description: "Unauthorized"
        "403":
          description: "Forbidden"
        "404":
          description: "Not Found"
        "415":
          description: "Unsupported media-type"
        "422":
          description: "Unprocessable"
          headers:
            correlationid:
              $ref: "#/components/headers/correlationIdResponseType"
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/VPDReturnDisplay_ETMPErrorType_Schema"
              examples:
                unprocessable:
                  value:
                    error:
                      processingDate: "2026-01-31T09:26:17Z"
                      code: "002"
                      text: "ID Number missing or invalid"
        "500":
          description: "Internal Server Error"
          headers:
            correlationid:
              $ref: "#/components/headers/correlationIdResponseType"
          content:
            application/json:
              schema:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/VPDReturn_SystemErrorType_Schema"
              examples:
                internalServerError:
                  $ref: "#/components/examples/SystemErrorType_500Sample"
components:
  headers:
    correlationIdResponseType:
      description: "Unique alphanumeric number used for correlation purposes. Generated\
        \ by the originating system and included in the response. Conforms to 36-character\
        \ UUID (formatted)"
      style: "simple"
      required: false
      deprecated: false
      schema:
        type: "string"
        pattern: "[0-9a-f]{8}-[0-9a-f]{4}-[0-5][0-9a-f]{3}-[089ab][0-9a-f]{3}-[0-9a-f]{12}"
  parameters:
    correlationid:
      name: "correlationid"
      in: "header"
      description: "A unique alphanumeric acknowledgement reference used for correlation\
        \ purposes.\nThis identifier must be generated by the originating system and\
        \ must conform to the standard 36-character UUID format.\n"
      required: true
      deprecated: false
      allowEmptyValue: false
      style: "simple"
      schema:
        type: "string"
        pattern: "^[0-9a-fA-F]{8}-[0-9a-fA-F]{4}-[0-9a-fA-F]{4}-[0-9a-fA-F]{4}-[0-9a-fA-F]{12}$"
      example: "f0bd1f32-de51-45cc-9b18-0520d6e3ab1a"
    X-Originating-System:
      name: "X-Originating-System"
      in: "header"
      description: "\"System that originates the request.\""
      required: true
      deprecated: false
      allowEmptyValue: false
      style: "simple"
      schema:
        type: "string"
        enum:
        - "MDTP"
    X-Receipt-Date:
      name: "X-Receipt-Date"
      in: "header"
      description: "Timestamp when the request message was created by the originating\
        \ system.\n Must be in UTC and follow ISO-8601 date-time format.\n"
      required: true
      deprecated: false
      allowEmptyValue: false
      style: "simple"
      schema:
        type: "string"
        format: "date-time"
    X-Regime-Type:
      name: "X-Regime-Type"
      in: "header"
      description: "\"Tax regime identifier.\""
      required: true
      deprecated: false
      allowEmptyValue: false
      style: "simple"
      schema:
        type: "string"
        enum:
        - "VPD"
    X-Transmitting-System:
      name: "X-Transmitting-System"
      in: "header"
      description: "\"Intermediary system that transmits the message.\""
      required: true
      deprecated: false
      allowEmptyValue: false
      style: "simple"
      schema:
        type: "string"
        enum:
        - "HIP"
    X-ZVPD:
      name: "X-ZVPD"
      in: "header"
      description: "Vaping Duty Reference Number.\nPattern: (GB|XI)WK followed by\
        \ 7 digits and suffix WK.\n"
      required: true
      deprecated: false
      allowEmptyValue: false
      style: "simple"
      schema:
        type: "string"
        pattern: "^(GB|XI)WK[0-9]{7}WK$"
  schemas:
    amountType11_2:
      description: "Currency - Total digit 11 with 2 decimal place"
      type: "number"
      minimum: 0
      maximum: 9.9999999999E8
      multipleOf: 0.01
    amountType9_4:
      type: "number"
      minimum: 0
      maximum: 99999.9999
      multipleOf: 1.0E-4
    amountTypeSigned11_2:
      description: "Signed currency amount (11 digits, 2 decimal places). Can be positive\
        \ or negative."
      type: "number"
      minimum: -9.9999999999E8
      maximum: 9.9999999999E8
      multipleOf: 0.01
    chargeReferenceType:
      type: "string"
      pattern: "^[A-Z]{2}[0-9]{12}([0-9]{2})?$"
    dateOnlyType:
      type: "string"
      format: "date"
    dateTimeType:
      type: "string"
      format: "date-time"
    declarationType:
      type: "object"
      properties:
        fullName:
          type: "string"
          maxLength: 120
        capacityInWhichSigned:
          type: "string"
          maxLength: 100
        signeesEmailAddress:
          type: "string"
          maxLength: 132
          format: "email"
      required:
      - "fullName"
      - "capacityInWhichSigned"
      - "signeesEmailAddress"
      additionalProperties: false
    dutyRateType:
      type: "number"
      minimum: 0
      maximum: 9999999.99
      multipleOf: 0.01
    otherOptionsType:
      description: "Details about duty suspense. If vapingProductUnderDutySuspense\
        \ = '1', then both volumeMovedFromDutySuspense and volumeMovedToDutySuspense\
        \ must be provided. If '0', these fields should not be provided."
      type: "object"
      properties:
        vapingProductUnderDutySuspense:
          $ref: "#/components/schemas/yesNoFlagType"
        volumeMovedFromDutySuspense:
          $ref: "#/components/schemas/amountType9_4"
        volumeMovedToDutySuspense:
          $ref: "#/components/schemas/amountType9_4"
      required:
      - "vapingProductUnderDutySuspense"
      additionalProperties: false
    overDecl:
      description: "Indicates whether over declaration applies. If overDeclFilled\
        \ = '1', then reasonForOverDecl must be provided and overDeclarationProducts\
        \ must contain at least one item. If '0', these fields should not be provided."
      type: "object"
      properties:
        overDeclFilled:
          $ref: "#/components/schemas/yesNoFlagType"
        reasonForOverDecl:
          $ref: "#/components/schemas/reasonType"
        overDeclarationProducts:
          type: "array"
          items:
            type: "object"
            properties:
              returnPeriodAffected:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/periodType"
              taxType:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/taxType"
              dutyRate:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/dutyRateType"
              amountOverDeclared:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/amountType9_4"
              dutyDue:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/amountType11_2"
            required:
            - "returnPeriodAffected"
            - "taxType"
            - "dutyRate"
            - "amountOverDeclared"
            - "dutyDue"
            additionalProperties: false
      required:
      - "overDeclFilled"
      additionalProperties: false
    periodType:
      type: "string"
      pattern: "^[0-9]{2}(KA|KB|KC|KD|KE|KF|KG|KH|KI|KJ|KK|KL)$"
    reasonType:
      type: "string"
      minLength: 1
      maxLength: 250
    spoiltProd:
      description: "If spoiltProductFilled = '1', then spoiltProducts must be present."
      type: "object"
      properties:
        spoiltProductFilled:
          $ref: "#/components/schemas/yesNoFlagType"
        spoiltProducts:
          type: "array"
          items:
            type: "object"
            properties:
              returnPeriodAffected:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/periodType"
              taxType:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/taxType"
              dutyRate:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/dutyRateType"
              amountSpoilt:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/amountType9_4"
              dutyDue:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/amountType11_2"
            required:
            - "returnPeriodAffected"
            - "taxType"
            - "dutyRate"
            - "amountSpoilt"
            - "dutyDue"
            additionalProperties: false
      required:
      - "spoiltProductFilled"
      additionalProperties: false
    submissionIdType:
      type: "string"
      pattern: "^[0-9]{12}$"
    successType:
      description: "Response when HTTP status code is 201"
      type: "object"
      properties:
        processingDate:
          $ref: "#/components/schemas/dateTimeType"
        vpdReferenceNumber:
          $ref: "#/components/schemas/vpdReferenceNumberType"
        submissionId:
          $ref: "#/components/schemas/submissionIdType"
        chargeReference:
          $ref: "#/components/schemas/chargeReferenceType"
        amount:
          $ref: "#/components/schemas/amountType11_2"
        paymentDueDate:
          $ref: "#/components/schemas/dateOnlyType"
      required:
      - "processingDate"
      - "vpdReferenceNumber"
      - "amount"
      - "paymentDueDate"
      additionalProperties: false
    taxType:
      type: "string"
      pattern: "^[A-Z0-9]{3}$"
    totalDutyDue:
      type: "object"
      properties:
        totalDutyDueVapingProducts:
          $ref: "#/components/schemas/amountType11_2"
        totalDutyOverDeclaration:
          $ref: "#/components/schemas/amountType11_2"
        totalDutyUnderDeclaration:
          $ref: "#/components/schemas/amountType11_2"
        totalDutySpoiltProduct:
          $ref: "#/components/schemas/amountType11_2"
        adjustmentAmount:
          description: "Net adjustment applied to the return. Positive increases liability;\
            \ negative reduces liability."
          $ref: "#/components/schemas/amountTypeSigned11_2"
        totalDue:
          description: "Final net amount. Positive indicates payable amount; negative\
            \ indicates repayment due."
          $ref: "#/components/schemas/amountTypeSigned11_2"
      required:
      - "totalDutyDueVapingProducts"
      - "totalDutyOverDeclaration"
      - "totalDutyUnderDeclaration"
      - "totalDutySpoiltProduct"
      - "adjustmentAmount"
      - "totalDue"
      additionalProperties: false
    underDecl:
      description: "Indicates whether under declaration applies. If underDeclFilled\
        \ = '1', then reasonForUnderDecl must be provided and underDeclarationProducts\
        \ must contain at least one item. If '0', these fields should not be provided."
      type: "object"
      properties:
        underDeclFilled:
          $ref: "#/components/schemas/yesNoFlagType"
        reasonForUnderDecl:
          $ref: "#/components/schemas/reasonType"
        underDeclarationProducts:
          type: "array"
          items:
            type: "object"
            properties:
              returnPeriodAffected:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/periodType"
              taxType:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/taxType"
              dutyRate:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/dutyRateType"
              amountUnderDeclared:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/amountType9_4"
              dutyDue:
                $ref: "#/components/schemas/amountType11_2"
            required:
            - "returnPeriodAffected"
            - "taxType"
            - "dutyRate"
            - "amountUnderDeclared"
            - "dutyDue"
            additionalProperties: false
      required:
      - "underDeclFilled"
      additionalProperties: false
    vapingReturns:
      description: "The vapingProdManufactured flag is defined at the parent level\
        \ and indicates whether any vaping products were manufactured during the return\
        \ period. If the flag is '1', the returns array contains one or more entries\
        \ with production details per tax type and duty rate combination. If the flag\
        \ is '0', the returns array must be empty"
      type: "array"
      minItems: 0
      items:
        type: "object"
        properties:
          taxType:
            $ref: "#/components/schemas/taxType"
          dutyRate:
            $ref: "#/components/schemas/dutyRateType"
          amountProducedLiquid:
            $ref: "#/components/schemas/amountType9_4"
          dutyDue:
            $ref: "#/components/schemas/amountType11_2"
        required:
        - "taxType"
        - "dutyRate"
        - "amountProducedLiquid"
        - "dutyDue"
        additionalProperties: false
    vpdReferenceNumberType:
      type: "string"
      pattern: "^(GB|XI)WK\\d{7}WK$"
    VPDReturn_SystemErrorType_Schema:
